there is no reason why the full length of the extreme period, as given officially by the Meteorological organization cannot be used.
If you say the record low is -3.8°C, weather box needs to reflect that. There is absolutely no reason why the full length of extremes should not be used.
Mean maximum is the highest temperature in each respective month over a set recording period divided by the length of that period, it is not simply the warmest highs and coldest lows.
This data is official, as it is the full length of the recording period from 1942 to present, rather than just 1981-2016.
